# Typography: Heading (Outfit) and Body (Switzer) typescale

The scale is **responsive**: **sm** (default, mobile) and **lg** (from `min-width: 768px`). Base size **16px = 1rem**. Variables live in the design system [src/app/design-system/theme.css](src/app/design-system/theme.css) and [src/app/globals.css](src/app/globals.css). The design system defines `--font-display` (Outfit) and `--font-body` (Switzer); globals maps `--font-heading` to Outfit for compatibility.

## 1. Embed in `<head>` (required)

**Outfit (headings):** In the HTML `<head>` (or in a CSS file loaded by the root HTML), include:

```html
<style>
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Outfit:wght@100..900&display=swap');
</style>
```

Use Tailwind utility **`font-heading`** for heading family (weight 600), or `font-family: var(--font-heading);` in custom CSS.

**Switzer (body):** In `<head>`, embed the project’s `@font-face` rules (see [src/app/globals.css](src/app/globals.css)). Set default body to `font-family: var(--font-body);` (e.g. `'Switzer-Variable', 'Switzer-Regular', sans-serif`). Use Tailwind utility **`font-body`** when applying body family without the full scale.

## 2. Heading typescale

Use **Outfit**, font-weight **600**. Semantic `<h1>`–`<h6>` and `<small>` get the scale from base CSS. Use **`font-heading`** when you need the heading family with a custom size.

**Sm (default):**

| Heading | font-size | line-height | letter-spacing |
| ------- | --------- | ------------ | -------------- |
| h1 | 32px | 1.3 | -0.01em |
| h2 | 28px | 1.3 | -0.01em |
| h3 | 26px | 1.3 | -0.01em |
| h4 | 22px | 1.3 | -0.01em |
| h5 | 20px | 1.3 | -0.01em |
| h6 | 18px | 1.3 | -0.01em |

**Lg (768px and up):**

| Heading | font-size | line-height | letter-spacing |
| ------- | --------- | ------------ | -------------- |
| h1 | 62px | 1.1 | -0.011em |
| h2 | 48px | 1.1 | -0.011em |
| h3 | 40px | 1.1 | -0.011em |
| h4 | 32px | 1.1 | -0.011em |
| h5 | 26px | 1.1 | -0.011em |
| h6 | 20px | 1.1 | -0.011em |

**Utility classes .h7–.h12** (unchanged sizes, use scale line-height/tracking): 2.25rem, 2rem, 1.875rem, 1.75rem, 1.5rem, 1.25rem.

## 3. Body and small

**Body:** 16px, line-height 1.6 (sm) / 1.5 (lg), letter-spacing 0. **Small:** 14px (sm) / 12px (lg).

Use **`.body-xl`**, **`.body-lg`**, **`.body-md`**, **`.body-sm`**, **`.body-xs`**, **`.body-xx`** for body tiers (font sizes 1.25rem → 0.625rem); they use the scale’s line-height and letter-spacing. Weights 400, 500, 600, 700 as needed.

## 4. Tailwind usage

- Prefer semantic **`<h1>`–`<h6>`** and **`<small>`** so they pick up the responsive base styles.
- Use **`font-heading`** and **`font-body`** when applying family without the full scale (e.g. custom text sizes).
- Responsive behaviour is built into the base CSS; no need to add `md:` for heading/body sizes on elements.

## 5. CSS reference (variable-based, in globals.css)

Base typography uses `:root` variables and one `@media (min-width: 768px)` block. Summary:

```css
html { font-size: var(--text-base-sm); }

body {
  font-family: var(--font-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-body);
  line-height: var(--line-height-body-sm);
  font-size: var(--text-base-sm);
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-body-sm);
}

h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  font-family: var(--font-heading);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-heading);
  line-height: var(--line-height-heading-sm);
  letter-spacing: var(--tracking-heading-sm);
}
h1 { font-size: var(--text-h1-sm); }
h2 { font-size: var(--text-h2-sm); }
h3 { font-size: var(--text-h3-sm); }
h4 { font-size: var(--text-h4-sm); }
h5 { font-size: var(--text-h5-sm); }
h6 { font-size: var(--text-h6-sm); }
small { font-size: var(--text-sm-sm); }

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  body {
    font-size: var(--text-base-lg);
    line-height: var(--line-height-body-lg);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-body-lg);
  }
  h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
    line-height: var(--line-height-heading-lg);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-heading-lg);
  }
  h1 { font-size: var(--text-h1-lg); }
  h2 { font-size: var(--text-h2-lg); }
  h3 { font-size: var(--text-h3-lg); }
  h4 { font-size: var(--text-h4-lg); }
  h5 { font-size: var(--text-h5-lg); }
  h6 { font-size: var(--text-h6-lg); }
  small { font-size: var(--text-sm-lg); }
}
```

`.body-xl` … `.body-xx` and `.h7` … `.h12` are defined in [src/app/globals.css](src/app/globals.css) using the same variables.
